         <div>
            <head>21.3.1882 Dienstag</head>
            <p>
               <placeName type="write" key="49097">Ascot</placeName> March 21. 1882. Tuesday</p>
            <p> We went to the Crystal Palace electric
               exhibition. The electric lights were very fine. We began by trying the telephone but
               the man at the other end would not connect us so we shouted abusive language down it.
               We had dinner with <persName key="1119">M<hi rend="ul.2">
                     <hi rend="sup">r</hi>
                  </hi> Sellon</persName> in the <orgName>Crystal Palace dining room</orgName>. I
               sat between <persName key="1120">Miss Sellon</persName> and <persName key="916">Jay</persName>. The finest thing we saw was the great brush light (which, by the
               way, is said to have hissed <persName key="5696">Gladstone</persName> when he was
               here, yesterday); it has a power of 150000 candles; the Alhambra court is also
               prettily lighted. I wrote an account of this in <name type="periodical" key="70792">the Gazette</name>
               <note type="reg">
                  <name type="periodical" key="70792">St. George´s Gazette</name>
               </note>
            </p>
         </div>
